    "Avram Glazer and his five siblings sold a quarter of their 68% stake in Manchester United to British chemicals billionaire Jim Ratcliffe in 2023.",
    "The deal valued the team at $5.4 billion (net of debt). Their father, shopping mall magnate Malcolm Glazer (d. 2014), bought the team for $1.4 billion in 2005.",
    "The Glazer siblings still own the NFL's Tampa Bay Buccaneers; their father acquired the franchise for $192 million in 1995, and it's now worth an estimated $5.2 billion (net of debt).",
    "Avram co-chairs Man U with brother Joel. Joel co-chairs the Bucs with brothers Bryan and Edward. Another brother, Kevin, runs the family's real estate arm, Glazer Properties.",
    "Sister Darcie Glazer Kassewitz is chairman of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers Foundation and two other family charitable foundations."
